1.title: Julian Broadus: The Apple Doesn't Fall Far from the Dogg Tree

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: 1 year later, Jackie Elam follows up with Snoop Dogg's son, Julian Broadus to see what he's been up to. We learn about his ambitions and his deep-seated passion for all things weed.

1.title: Kid Biz with Hollywood Agent, Cactus McCallum and Hollywood Mom, Kim Biel

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: Jackie's guests include top Hollywood Model/Talent Agent, Cactus McCallum of Cactus Creatives Los Angeles (CCLA) and Hollywood Mom, Kim Biel. The pros discuss how to get an agent for your kids, avoid scams, and keep kids safe in the biz.

2.title: Snoop Dogg's Son, Julian Broadus + Rap Artist, P.O.E.M.

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

2.plot: Snoop Dogg's son, Julian Broadus and Rap Artist, P.O.E.M. in studio to discuss the struggles, pressure and hustle of making it in the biz. From Julian, who is just starting out trying to make a name for himself as a multi-faceted Talent (despite 5 already famous relatives), to P.O.E.M. who recently played LA Live, making it on his own by networking (and his infectious smile), the two connect on the topics of poetry, various music genres and just "getting out there".

3.title: Hollywood Manager, Heidi Rotbart

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

3.plot: Hollywood Personal/Talent Manager, Heidi Rotbart shares her story of her start in Hollywood with the Legendary Comedian, Phyllis Diller, which led to a career managing comedic talent and performers.

4.title: BizParentz: Anne Henry + Paula Dorn

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

4.plot: Child Performer Advocates, Anne Henry and Paula Dorn of BizParentz Foundation, talk about current child industry news and ways to keep children safe in the biz.

5.title: Network Executives and Philanthropists, Daphna Edwards Ziman and Dagmara Almand

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

5.plot: Network Executives and Philanthropists, Daphna Edwards Ziman and Dagmara Almand talk about the FCC, Owning a Network > Cinemoi, their award winning coverage of The Inter-Nations Fashion Film Awards, and the importance of Philanthropy.

6.title: Actor, Antwon Tanner

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

6.plot: Antwon Tanner talks about his start in the industry. He is best known for his recurring role as Michael on Moesha, and its spinoff The Parkers, and as Antwon "Skills" Taylor on One Tree Hill. He is currently on Black Jesus.

7.title: The Oscar Nod Edition: Claus Toksvig Kjaer

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

7.plot: Oscar-Nominated Animation Producer, Claus Toksvig Kjaer of Denmark's Animation Studio, Norlum. Claus talks about Norlum and Cartoon Saloon's co-production, "Song of the Sea" which won 40 awards and received a coveted Academy Award Nomination. Claus also discusses his latest film, "Long Way North" playing in select cities in French and English.

8.title: Actor Jeff Daly and Actress Tasha Dixon

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

8.plot: Jeff Daly talks about Writing, Directing, Acting and his love of short films. Tasha Dixon discusses her Writing and Acting Career as well as the backlash of speaking out against the inappropriate behavior she witnessed of a 2016 Presidential Candidate.

9.title: Kid Biz: Jeffrey Vinokur, Dancing Scientist

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

9.plot: Jeffrey Vinokur, Dancing Scientist pops, locks and explodes stuff with several 8-10 year old kiddos on this FUN episode of JACKIE ELAM LIVE! Entertainment Unlimited

10.title: Recording Artist, EJ

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

10.plot: Recording Artist, EJ, writer/singer of Jackie's theme song, "Tune In Now" is the special guest. EJ performs his song, "Saucy" and talks about his team of 16, his drive, the Premiere of "Fresh off The Press" with Bobby Brown Jr, ending with EJ's music video "One Day".

11.title: Dave Brown, Founder of Indie Night Film Festival

episode of.title: Jackie Elam Live! Entertainment Unlimited (TV Series 2016– )

11.plot: Dave Brown discusses how Hollywood builds people up then tears them down. His purpose is to build people up, provided a weekly platform to showcase their work: Indie Night Film Festival at TCL Chinese Theater. Actress/Filmmaker, Eman Miller, joins the conversation.
